description._content:
Back page of program for Deseronto High School's Commencement of November 25, 1958. The event was held at the Bayview [Naylor's] Theatre, Deseronto, Ontario.

"Deseronto Board of Education
S. E. Knapp - Chairman, Mrs. Peter Thielman, Mrs. Edith Therrien, Mrs. Estelle Jackson, H. J. Fingland, A. B. Harvey, D. S. Armitage, Mrs. Madeline Babcocke - Secretary-Treasurer

Deseronto High School Staff
Eric L. Quirk, B.A.K.I.H - Princripal, Miss Irene Lockie, B. A., M. J. Rutherford, B.A., Mrs Izobel MacTavish

Deseronto High School Students' Council
President: Robert Handley
Vice-President: Barry Browning
Secretary: Moira Alford
Treasurer: Charles French
Grade XII Representative: Alberta Marks, James Bell
Grade XI Representative: Madelyn Watters, Norman Babcooke
Grade X Representative: Catherine Murphy, Roger Cole
Grade IX Representative: Lorraine Harvey, Bert Sly

The thanks of the High School are extended to Mrs. Foster, Mrs. Ungar, Mrs. G. Stuart, and Mrs. Bender for their kind assistance in the preparation of costumes.

Printed by THE POST-EXPRESS, Napanee"


Item donated by Bev Boomhour, November 2010.
